</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="85" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,905]" box="[199,887,592,617]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,592,617]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">Etymology:</emphasis>
This new species is named after its 
<typeStatus box="[742,790,593,617]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,905]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,628,653]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">Affinities</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Abu El-Hassan &amp; Badrawy &amp; Fadl &amp; Mohammad, 2019" authorityName="Abu El-Hassan &amp; Badrawy &amp; Fadl &amp; Mohammad" authorityYear="2019" box="[327,548,628,653]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Atylotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shagrensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[327,548,628,653]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">Atylotus shagrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[558,651,628,653]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[558,651,628,653]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is closely related to the Egyptian species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wiedemann, 1828)" authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1828" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1828" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Atylotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agricola">
<emphasis box="[1146,1275,628,653]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">A. agricola</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wiedemann, C." pageId="6" pageNumber="85" refId="ref6440" refString="Wiedemann, C. (1828) Ausssereuropaische zweiflugelige Insecten. Als Fortsetzung des Meigenschen Werks. Erster Theil, Schulz, Hamm, xxxii + 608 pp." type="book" year="1828">Wiedemann, 1828</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and the European species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Villeneuve), 1920" authorityName="Villeneuve" authorityYear="1920" baseAuthorityName="Villeneuve" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[541,918,664,689]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Atylotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loewianus">
<emphasis box="[541,691,664,689]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">A. loewianus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Villeneuve, J." box="[711,918,664,689]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" pagination="60 - 65" refId="ref6220" refString="Villeneuve, J. (1920) Sur Ochrops (Atylotus) fulvus Meigen. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 1920, 60 - 65." type="journal article" year="1920">Villeneuve), 1920</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
because of the parallel-sided frons and the abdominal pattern. The new species can be easily separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1828" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[932,1062,700,725]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Atylotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agricola">
<emphasis box="[932,1062,700,725]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">A. agricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of frontal calli, blackish colour of frons, polished brown colour of subcallus and reddish-brown colour of the abdomen. 
<taxonomicName authority="Abu El-Hassan &amp; Badrawy &amp; Fadl &amp; Mohammad, 2019" authorityName="Abu El-Hassan &amp; Badrawy &amp; Fadl &amp; Mohammad" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Atylotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shagrensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">Atylotus shagrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[282,377,772,797]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[282,377,772,797]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Villeneuve" authorityYear="1920" baseAuthorityName="Villeneuve" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[649,798,772,797]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Atylotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loewianus">
<emphasis box="[649,798,772,797]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">A. loewianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the hairy eyes, absence of frontal calli, colour of subcallus and frons, and reddish-brown colour of the abdomen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="85" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,905]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,844,869]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">Remarks.</emphasis>
Four female specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Villeneuve" authorityName="Villeneuve" authorityYear="1920" baseAuthorityName="Villeneuve" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[663,1024,844,869]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Atylotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loewianus">
<emphasis box="[663,884,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">Atylotus loewianus</emphasis>
Villeneuve
</taxonomicName>
, which were collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1354,1436,844,869]" name="Croatia" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">Croatia</collectingCountry>
(
<date box="[159,295,880,905]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" value="1996-08-08">8.VIII.1996</date>
), were sent to us for examination by Prof. Dr. Stjepan Krčmar from his personal collection (SKC).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
